docs.abstract: The former Minneapolis police officer Derek Chauvin was found guilty of murder and manslaughter charges in the death of George Floyd, a Black man whose killing sparked nationwide protests.
docs.snippet: The former Minneapolis police officer Derek Chauvin was found guilty of murder and manslaughter charges in the death of George Floyd, a Black man whose killing sparked nationwide protests.
docs.lead_paragraph: The former Minneapolis police officer Derek Chauvin was found guilty of murder and manslaughter charges in the death of George Floyd, a Black man whose killing sparked nationwide protests.

headline.main: Derek Chauvin Found Guilty of Murder

docs.abstract: On Wednesday, James Reyerson, the Minnesota law enforcement agent in charge of investigating George Floyd’s death, testified about how he collected information at the scene of the arrest.
docs.snippet: On Wednesday, James Reyerson, the Minnesota law enforcement agent in charge of investigating George Floyd’s death, testified about how he collected information at the scene of the arrest.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, James Reyerson, the Minnesota law enforcement agent in charge of investigating George Floyd’s death, testified about how he collected information at the scene of the arrest.

headline.main: Minnesota Law Enforcement Agent James Reyerson Testifies

docs.abstract: Morries Hall, a friend of George Floyd who was with him when he was arrested, is hoping to avoid testifying. On Tuesday, Mr. Hall’s legal team stated he planned to invoke his Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination.

headline.main: Morries Hall, George Floyd’s Friend, Hopes to Avoid Chauvin Trial Testimony

docs.abstract: Dr. Bradford Wankhede Langenfeld, the emergency room physician who cared for George Floyd the day he died, testified about Mr. Floyd’s condition when he reached the hospital.
docs.snippet: Dr. Bradford Wankhede Langenfeld, the emergency room physician who cared for George Floyd the day he died, testified about Mr. Floyd’s condition when he reached the hospital.
docs.lead_paragraph: Dr. Bradford Wankhede Langenfeld, the emergency room physician who cared for George Floyd the day he died, testified about Mr. Floyd’s condition when he reached the hospital.

headline.main: George Floyd’s Emergency Room Physician Testifies in Chauvin Trial

docs.abstract: Sgt. Jody Stiger of the Los Angeles Police Department and an expert on the use of force, testified on Wednesday about reasonable force in the arrest of George Floyd.
docs.snippet: Sgt. Jody Stiger of the Los Angeles Police Department and an expert on the use of force, testified on Wednesday about reasonable force in the arrest of George Floyd.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sgt. Jody Stiger of the Los Angeles Police Department and an expert on the use of force, testified on Wednesday about reasonable force in the arrest of George Floyd.

headline.main: Expert: ‘No Force’ Should’ve Been Used Once Floyd Was Restrained

docs.abstract: A veteran pulmonologist Dr. Martin J. Tobin testified that George Floyd’s death was caused in part by Derek Chauvin’s knees pressing against his neck and back, making it impossible for him to breathe.

headline.main: Pulmonologist Details How George Floyd Lost Consciousness During Arrest

docs.abstract: Michelle Moseng, a retired paramedic, testified about George Floyd’s condition after a 2019 arrest, saying Mr. Floyd told her he had been taking some form of opioid. Her testimony was limited to the physical effects of opioids on Mr. Floyd.

docs.abstract: Dr. Bill Smock, a surgeon for the Louisville Metropolitan Police Department, testified on Thursday that he had found no evidence to support claims that George Floyd died of an overdose.
docs.snippet: Dr. Bill Smock, a surgeon for the Louisville Metropolitan Police Department, testified on Thursday that he had found no evidence to support claims that George Floyd died of an overdose.
docs.lead_paragraph: Dr. Bill Smock, a surgeon for the Louisville Metropolitan Police Department, testified on Thursday that he had found no evidence to support claims that George Floyd died of an overdose.

headline.main: Police Surgeon Says George Floyd Died of Asphyxia

docs.abstract: Dr. Lindsey Thomas, a forensic pathologist, testified on Friday that police restraint killed George Floyd, primarily by restricting his oxygen with a secondary effect of physiological stress on his body.

headline.main: Forensic Pathologist Says Physiologic Stress Contributed to Floyd’s Death

docs.abstract: Keith Ellison, the attorney general of Minnesota, thanked George Floyd’s family after Derek Chauvin was found guilty. Mr. Ellison also encouraged peaceful reactions to the verdict.
